00:53:10.080 --> 00:53:13.200
One of the interesting-- if I
can just free associate for one

00:53:13.200 --> 00:53:15.760
moment, it's interesting to
think about this in relation

00:53:15.760 --> 00:53:18.600
to language.

00:53:18.600 --> 00:53:20.650
One of the big questions
that people have always

00:53:20.650 --> 00:53:23.266
asked about language--
not always asked,

00:53:23.266 --> 00:53:26.320
but I'm thinking of sort of
people in the post Chomskian

00:53:26.320 --> 00:53:28.300
world of linguistics
have asked--

00:53:28.300 --> 00:53:31.820
how is it that we can learn
language as readily as we can,

00:53:31.820 --> 00:53:33.990
given our complexities and
given how little time we

00:53:33.990 --> 00:53:37.135
have to learn it and given how
poor the linguistic samples are

00:53:37.135 --> 00:53:38.960
on the basis of which
we do learn it--

00:53:38.960 --> 00:53:43.610
baby talk and inaccurate speech
as people slur their words when

00:53:43.610 --> 00:53:44.970
they're talking.

00:53:44.970 --> 00:53:49.178
And yet kids get it,
and they get it fast.

00:53:49.178 --> 00:53:51.950
Well, there's an interesting
way of turning that idea around

00:53:51.950 --> 00:53:52.490
on its head.

00:53:52.490 --> 00:53:54.590
This is not an idea
original to me.

00:53:54.590 --> 00:53:56.840
There's an interesting way
of turning that idea around

00:53:56.840 --> 00:53:59.070
on its head, which is
that language, in a way,

00:53:59.070 --> 00:54:00.990
is a user friendly system.

00:54:00.990 --> 00:54:05.660
It's been designed through
thousands of years precisely

00:54:05.660 --> 00:54:08.110
to be learnable by
creatures like us.

00:54:08.110 --> 00:54:11.560
So it's not that
we are so smart.

00:54:11.560 --> 00:54:13.490
It's that the design
process iterated

00:54:13.490 --> 00:54:17.615
over long periods of time has
turned out to be so sufficient.

00:54:20.280 --> 00:54:24.080
And I think something actually
similar-- in the book,

00:54:24.080 --> 00:54:27.320
