00:54:59.370 --> 00:55:06.390
that because they tap into
the way we naturally see?

00:55:06.390 --> 00:55:09.100
Or is it that they've
taught how to see

00:55:09.100 --> 00:55:11.420
in the way in which a
virtual environment can teach

00:55:11.420 --> 00:55:15.340
a gamer or a user how to act?

00:55:15.340 --> 00:55:16.930
AUDIENCE: The sort
of reorganization

00:55:16.930 --> 00:55:19.390
that you describe as
occurring through art

00:55:19.390 --> 00:55:23.100
is something that reminds
me of what happens

00:55:23.100 --> 00:55:27.150
with education,
with psychotherapy,

00:55:27.150 --> 00:55:31.880
with other sorts of situations
where you achieve an insight

00:55:31.880 --> 00:55:34.120
and then you have this
nonlinear transition

00:55:34.120 --> 00:55:36.580
in your understanding of things.

00:55:36.580 --> 00:55:39.570
Do you see those as part
of the same category?

00:55:39.570 --> 00:55:42.350
And if so, why did
you pick art as sort

00:55:42.350 --> 00:55:44.520
of the prototypical
example of it.

00:55:44.520 --> 00:55:47.430
ALVA NOE: The
discovery in the book

00:55:47.430 --> 00:55:49.090
is that there's a
phenomenon called

00:55:49.090 --> 00:55:50.335
reorganizational practice.

00:55:53.490 --> 00:55:58.260
And art is one and
so is philosophy.

00:55:58.260 --> 00:56:00.977
And by the way, that's not an
orthodox view in philosophy.

00:56:00.977 --> 00:56:02.560
I mean, there are
people in philosophy

00:56:02.560 --> 00:56:04.010
that would agree with me.

00:56:04.010 --> 00:56:07.240
But many philosophers
think of themselves

00:56:07.240 --> 00:56:11.410
as seeking knowledge or
results or making proofs

00:56:11.410 --> 00:56:15.550
about the nature of mind
and matter and causation.

00:56:15.550 --> 00:56:21.270
The idea that philosophy is
not about discovering truths

00:56:21.270 --> 00:56:26.140
but is about reorganizing
us is a debatable view.

00:56:30.890 --> 00:56:33.490
The argument of the book is
that art and philosophy matter

00:56:33.490 --> 00:56:37.070
to us, because they are
reorganizational practices.

00:56:37.070 --> 00:56:39.610
If the value of philosophy
depended on the truths

00:56:39.610 --> 00:56:41.600
that philosophers had
established and come

00:56:41.600 --> 00:56:44.650
to agree upon, philosophy
would be in trouble.

00:56:44.650 --> 00:56:47.190
But it's not a
problem for philosophy

00:56:47.190 --> 00:56:52.220
that no philosopher agrees
with another philosopher.

00:56:52.220 --> 00:56:53.940
Similarly, it's
no problem for art

00:56:53.940 --> 00:56:59.240
that art doesn't converge
on a single artistic idea.

00:56:59.240 --> 00:57:00.807
So I think that
the idea that art

00:57:00.807 --> 00:57:02.890
is a reorganizational
practice and that philosophy

00:57:02.890 --> 00:57:05.224
are reorganizational
practices help

00:57:05.224 --> 00:57:07.640
us answer the kinds of questions
I asked at the beginning.

00:57:07.640 --> 00:57:08.690
What is art?

00:57:08.690 --> 00:57:10.140
What is philosophy?

00:57:10.140 --> 00:57:11.210
Why do they matter to us?

00:57:11.210 --> 00:57:13.282
What do they teach
us about ourselves?

00:57:13.282 --> 00:57:15.240
Now, you're asking a very
interesting question.

00:57:17.820 --> 00:57:20.370
Are there other
reorganizational practices?

00:57:20.370 --> 00:57:23.715
Is psychotherapy, for
example psychoanalysis,

00:57:23.715 --> 00:57:26.470
a reorganization practice?

00:57:26.470 --> 00:57:28.890
This terminology of
organization reorganization

00:57:28.890 --> 00:57:34.040
is used in a number
of other fields,

00:57:34.040 --> 00:57:36.330
for example, in the
body work field.

00:57:36.330 --> 00:57:38.430
People like Feldenkrais
practitioners

00:57:38.430 --> 00:57:40.900
talk about reorganizing
the body's habits

00:57:40.900 --> 00:57:43.140
to deal with organic
problems that the body faces.

00:57:48.400 --> 00:57:51.650
And I'm open to the
possibility that there

00:57:51.650 --> 00:57:56.825
are other species of the genus
than just art and philosophy.

00:58:00.440 --> 00:58:02.510
So my answer to you,
if that's the question,

00:58:02.510 --> 00:58:08.990
is I didn't mean to suggest
that I'd given evidence

00:58:08.990 --> 00:58:12.410
that only art and philosophy
are reorganizational practices.

00:58:12.410 --> 00:58:14.100
But now there's a
further question,

00:58:14.100 --> 00:58:16.830
which you might be asking.

00:58:16.830 --> 00:58:19.240
What's the principle of
differentiation between them?

00:58:23.300 --> 00:58:24.800
I thought about
that for a long time

00:58:24.800 --> 00:58:27.100
in a slightly different setting.

00:58:30.010 --> 00:58:33.080
Most of the features that
I think define works of art

00:58:33.080 --> 00:58:34.850
are also characteristics
of jokes.

00:58:38.530 --> 00:58:41.549
Jokes are sort of
cognitively rich.

00:58:41.549 --> 00:58:43.090
They involve certain
kinds of shifts.

00:58:45.955 --> 00:58:48.530
They exhibit many of the
hallmarks of works of art.

00:58:52.714 --> 00:58:54.380
I don't know if that's
a problem for me.

00:58:54.380 --> 00:58:59.610
Maybe joke-telling is a
species of art-making.

00:58:59.610 --> 00:59:04.404
But I would-- oh,
there's another way.

00:59:04.404 --> 00:59:06.320
Actually, here's another
point that's related.

00:59:06.320 --> 00:59:08.390
Sorry if my answer is
going on much too long.

00:59:08.390 --> 00:59:10.480
But another point
which is relevant

00:59:10.480 --> 00:59:16.450
is playing the flute
is an art form.

00:59:16.450 --> 00:59:18.970
Dancing hip hop is an art form.

00:59:18.970 --> 00:59:21.180
Potting is an art form.

00:59:21.180 --> 00:59:25.070
Making video installations
is an art form.

00:59:25.070 --> 00:59:27.140
Building buildings
is an art form.

00:59:27.140 --> 00:59:30.700
Those are all totally
different kinds of things.

00:59:30.700 --> 00:59:36.460
So maybe the class of things
that participate-- and I

00:59:36.460 --> 00:59:40.210
want to say that philosophy
belongs on that list-- what

00:59:40.210 --> 00:59:43.890
makes them each
art forms, I think,

00:59:43.890 --> 00:59:46.750
is the way in which
they're performing

00:59:46.750 --> 00:59:51.120
reorganizational work in
different neighborhoods

00:59:51.120 --> 00:59:51.821
of our being.

00:59:55.258 --> 01:00:00.150
And-- and maybe this
is getting closer

01:00:00.150 --> 01:00:04.600
to something that might have
been in the back of your mind--

01:00:04.600 --> 01:00:06.436
and they're doing so
for that reason alone.

01:00:12.600 --> 01:00:15.980
The artist isn't trying to get
a rocket ship to go to the moon

01:00:15.980 --> 01:00:17.130
or to debug a program.

01:00:20.600 --> 01:00:23.980
The artist, if I'm
right, is trying

01:00:23.980 --> 01:00:26.370
to give us
enlightenment, is trying

01:00:26.370 --> 01:00:31.850
to help us understand
ourselves, and in that sense,

01:00:31.850 --> 01:00:35.900
open up the possibility
of changing ourselves.

01:00:35.900 --> 01:00:37.670
Maybe that's a very
good explanation

01:00:37.670 --> 01:00:39.600
of what psychoanalysis
is doing too.

01:00:39.600 --> 01:00:40.560
That's a good question.

01:00:40.560 --> 01:00:43.120
It's an open question to me.

01:00:43.120 --> 01:00:44.020
[APPLAUSE]

01:00:44.020 --> 01:00:45.220
Thank you very much.

01:00:45.220 --> 01:00:47.670
I thank you for your attention.

